message.content:
A cardigan is a type of sweater that opens in the front with buttons or a zipper. 
It is usually made of wool, cotton, or synthetic fabrics. 
Cardigans come in various colors such as black, grey, blue, red, or green. 
They feature long sleeves and a V-neck or round neckline. 
Some cardigans have pockets on the front. 
Cardigans can be worn by both men and women and are often used as a layering item in colder weather. 
They can be found in casual or more formal settings, and are a popular item in fashion.
